  "title": "SAFETY COORDINATOR",
  "description": "<p><strong>Safety Coordinator (Singapore)</strong><br /><strong>Company:</strong> DONG CONSTRUCTION & ENGINEERING PTE LTD<br /><strong>Location:</strong> Singapore (site-based)<br /><strong>Employment Type:</strong> Full-time</p><h3>Role Overview</h3><p>DONG CONSTRUCTION & ENGINEERING PTE LTD is hiring a Safety Coordinator to execute day-to-day Workplace Safety & Health (WSH) controls on active project sites. This is a hands-on role focused on inspections, compliance enforcement, toolbox meetings, and closing out safety issues quickly and properly.</p><h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><ul><li><p>Conduct daily site safety inspections; identify unsafe acts/conditions and implement immediate controls.</p></li><li><p>Track, follow up, and close out corrective/preventive actions with site teams and subcontractors.</p></li><li><p>Support implementation of Risk Assessments (RA), Safe Work Procedures (SWP), Permit-to-Work (PTW), and WSH control measures.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate toolbox meetings, safety briefings, and site safety communications.</p></li><li><p>Monitor subcontractor compliance (PPE, housekeeping, method statements, site rules) and escalate when required.</p></li><li><p>Support incident/near-miss reporting and investigations (evidence collection, action tracking, learning points).</p></li><li><p>Maintain WSH documentation and registers (inspection reports, training records, PPE issuance, permits, etc.).</p></li><li><p>Assist with audits, site walkdowns, and alignment to client/main contractor safety requirements.</p></li><li><p>Track leading indicators and prepare basic WSH performance updates.</p></li></ul><h3>Requirements</h3><ul><li><p><strong>Minimum 3 years and above</strong> of relevant WSH/site safety experience, <strong>including experience working on LTA projects</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Working knowledge of common site safety systems: RA/SWP, PTW, toolbox meetings, inspections, audits.</p></li><li><p>WSQ WSH-related certification(s) preferred (e.g., Safety Coordinator / WSH training credentials).</p></li><li><p>Strong site presence with disciplined follow-through and documentation.</p></li><li><p>Able to communicate effectively with workers, supervisors, and subcontractors.</p></li><li><p>Comfortable with basic reporting (Word/Excel) and photo-based documentation.</p></li></ul><h3>Preferred</h3><ul><li><p>Experience supporting higher-risk activities (lifting operations, excavation, confined space, hot works, work-at-height).</p></li><li><p>Proven ability to drive closure—not just report issues.</p></li></ul><h3>What We Offer</h3><ul><li><p>Stable pipeline of projects and clear operational exposure.</p></li><li><p>Execution-first safety culture focused on practical controls and accountability.</p></li><li><p>Competitive salary package commensurate with experience.</p></li></ul><h3>How to Apply</h3><p>Email your <strong>CV</strong>, <strong>current/expected salary</strong>, and <strong>availability</strong> to <a href=\"mailto:careers@dongce.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">careers@dongce.com.sg</a> with subject: <strong>“Safety Coordinator – [Your Name]”</strong>.</p>",
